            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Significantly. WordStream data shows moving from a Quality Score of 5 to 8 can reduce CPC by 37%. The relationship is not linear — each point improvement above 5 produces compounding CPC reductions.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can I see Quality Score for all my keywords?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Open your Google Ads keyword report and add the Quality Score column. You can also add individual component columns (Expected CTR, Ad Relevance, Landing Page Experience) to identify exactly which component is dragging the score down.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does Quality Score matter for automated bidding?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The visible Quality Score is not used directly in Smart Bidding algorithms. However, the underlying signals — CTR history, ad relevance, landing page quality — factor into real-time auction calculations. Better fundamentals still improve outcomes under automated bidding.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
